contentfulExhibition.title: NfTNeTArT – from Net Art to Art NFT

childMarkdownRemark.html: NfTNeTArT – group show with Kim Asendorf, LaTurbo Avedon, Sarah Friend, LIA, Jonas Lund, Rhea Myers, Rafaël Rozendaal, Cornelia Sollfrank, Harm van den Dorpel

from Net Art to Art NFT

– a cooperation between panke.gallery and OFFICE IMPART

On the occasion of panke.gallery's 5 year anniversary, we trace back current discussions and developments in digital art and, making use of the multifaceted framework of generative art, draw a line from early netart activities to recent artistic interpretations and applications of blockchain art.

The exhibition NfTNeTArT – from Net Art to Art NFT brings together nine international artists that use algorithmic or generative systems as their artistic language. Their tools are digital codes and automatisms, which manifest themselves in a variety of unique and fascinating aesthetics. Confronting recent technologies and blockchain applications, the artists' strategies range from aesthetic or narrative, to critical or rather performative investigations. They equally explore the limits and possibilities of NFTs.
Featuring historical net art activities next to very recent works developed specifically for the occasion, the exhibition creates a dialogical environment in which classic network phenomena and cutting-edge technologies interact.

The exhibition has been developed in cooperation between panke.gallery and OFFICE IMPART and will be shown physically in both spaces and digitally at jpg.space. Supported by ZORA.

jpg.space allows everyone to create NFT exhibitions, regardless of whether they own the NFTs or not. Flexible layouts allow users to bring attention and value to NFTs through context, focused viewing experiences, and new, complementary meanings.

ZORA is the marketplace protocol for NFTs. The Zora protocol lets anyone create a permissionless and onchain marketplace for any NFT. Zora has a rich ecosystem of marketplaces, protocols and apps built on it, including PartyDAO, Mirror, Catalog and Artiva.
